 <purpose>
   <p>
     The Work request application module supports the requirement to request
     that an action be taken on a product or product data.
   </p>
   <p>
     Typical actions on the product or product data (product configuration
     information) may be: 
     <ul>
       <li>create;</li>
       <li>maintain;</li>
       <li>change;</li>
       <li>dispose.</li>
     </ul>
   </p>
   <p>
     Examples of product data for which a work_request may be identified are
     product support information, maintenance manuals, design drawings or
     design CAD models.
   </p>

 </purpose>

 <inscope>
   <li>
     the identification of requests for work to be
    carried out on a product or product data;
  </li>
  <li>
    the description of the issue that the work request is expected to
    address;
  </li>
  <li>
    the relationships between work requests;
  </li>
  <li>
    the versioning of work requests;
  </li>
  <li>the identification of items affected by the work request.</li>
  <!--
  <li>
   the characterization of the status assigned to a work request;
  </li>

       <li>the effectivity.</li>
       -->
 </inscope>

 <outscope>
   <li>
     the definition of the work that is to be undertaken;
     <note number="1">The definition is provided by the 
     <module_ref linkend="activity_method:1_scope">
       activity_method</module_ref> module.
   </note>
   </li>
   <li>
     the authority to undertake the work identified.
     <note number="2">The authority is provided by the 
     <module_ref linkend="work_order:1_scope">
       work_order</module_ref> module.
   </note>
   </li>
   <li>
     the approval of the work_request;
     <note number="3">
       The association of approvals to work_requests is provided by extending this module.
     </note>
   </li>
   <li>
     the date the work_request was raised;
     <note number="4">
       The association of dates to work_requests is provided by extending this module.
     </note>
   </li>
   <li>
     the person or organization that raised the the work_request.
     <note number="5">
       The association of a person or organization to work_requests is
       provided by extending this module. 
     </note>
   </li>
 </outscope>

